                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable F</hi> 20.) I was on duty in Holborn—I saw the two prisoners coming towards me—Clark had this coat, and the shop ticket of it in his hand—Way who was in company with him, saw me, and ran away across the road—I took Clark, and asked what he had got there—"Not much," he said—I said, "This is one of Mr. Prew's coats; you must come back with me"—I had known Way before—I saw him with Clark for about a minute that night, and I had seen them together before—they are constant companions.</p>
